# .graphifyignore — extra excludes for the graphify knowledge graph.
# https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify
#
# graphify already honors .gitignore automatically (node_modules/, dist/,
# src-tauri/target/, .env*, coverage/, .vite, *.cdx.json, ...), so this file only
# adds project-specific noise on top. Syntax matches .gitignore (incl. ! negation).

# Lockfiles: large, generated, no semantic value in a knowledge graph
pnpm-lock.yaml
src-tauri/Cargo.lock

# Generated Tauri output (mobile projects + bindings; kept in tree, not source of truth)
src-tauri/gen/

# graphify's own output — never graph the graph
graphify-out/

# Binary icon/image assets — keep extraction code-focused and fully offline.
# Image nodes require an LLM pass; delete these lines to include images in the graph.
*.png
*.ico
*.icns
*.webp

# graphify's own vendored skill + reference docs are tooling/meta (how to drive
# graphify), not Portcode product knowledge — keep them out of the graph so the
# map stays focused on the app's architecture. `.claude/settings.json` is NOT
# matched here, so the project's hook config still participates in the graph.
.claude/skills/

# Transient research deliverable (graphify recommendation write-up), not part of
# the product's documented architecture.
GRAPHIFY_NOTES.md
